        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 4:13PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>The combination of temperatures in the 90s combined with increasing
humidity associated with the inland moving sea breeze will
briefly push heat indices into the 114 to 118 range through 7 PM.
This will be make for dangerous conditions, especially if working
outside. Some communities that will be impacted include Awendaw,
Mount Pleasant, Daniel Island, Downtown Charleston, West Ashley,
James Island, Johns Island, Ravenel, Adams Run, Bennetts Point
and Jacksonboro.
</description>
        <instruction>Take extra precautions if you work or spend time outside. Know
the signs and symptoms of heat exhaustion and heat stroke. Wear
light weight and loose fitting clothing when possible and drink
plenty of water.</instruction>
